<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 04 at 3:07AM CDT  by NWS Austin-San Antonio</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Llano
County through 345 AM CDT...
At 307 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Prairie Mountain, or 19 miles north of Fredericksburg. This storm
was drifting south.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Prairie Mountain and Enchanted Rock State Natural Area.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
